Strategist Domdora: "Impossible! Why is the door closing!?"

Pony-Celes: "There's no escape now. Hand over \n[6] if you don't
want to get hurt!"
Strategist Domdora: "You're persistent. Still spouting nonsense!"

Pony-Celes: "If you're going to play dumb, then I have no choice.
Prepare yourself!"
Strategist Domdora: "It's come to this, huh..."
Strategist Domdora: "Let me show you why I am called the strategist!"

Strategist Domdora: "You let your guard down."

Strategist Domdora: "Now you can't move. Just like in the Avan
District."
Pony-Celes: "I won't lose just because of this!"
Strategist Domdora: "You can act tough all you want but..."
Strategist Domdora: "Well, do you know what this is?"
Pony-Celes: "How would I know? I don't even want to know!"

Strategist Domdora: "This is the bomb used to blow up the Avan
District."

Strategist Domdora: "And this is a miniaturized version of that bomb,
fashioned into a belt."

Strategist Domdora: "It may not have the power to blow up a city
but..."
Strategist Domdora: "It's more than enough to finish you off."
Strategist Domdora: "What's wrong? You've gone pale."
Strategist Domdora: "Even you must feel fear, right?"
Strategist Domdora: "Why not admit defeat gracefully?"
Pony-Celes: "I will never submit to someone like you!"

Strategist Domdora: "Then let's put it to the test. If you survive
this bomb, then justice wins."
Strategist Domdora: "In other words, it will be your victory."
Strategist Domdora: "See, it's scary, isn't it?"
Strategist Domdora: "This is my last piece of advice."

Strategist Domdora: "Beg for your life. If you do, I won't kill you.
You'll live as my servant."
Pony-Celes: "Who would ever submit to you!"

Strategist Domdora: "Foh foh foh, your so-called justice has been
blown to smithereens."
SV_ボイスのループ演奏 haiboku_s9_049
Strategist Domdora: "However, to not be dead after that explosion..."
Strategist Domdora: "There's still room for research with this bomb."

Strategist Domdora: "Well, well, it seems you can't maintain your
transformation."

Strategist Domdora: "To think you were so full of vigor, yet now you
expose your true form in front of the enemy, how disgraceful."
Strategist Domdora: "This is what happens when you defy me."

Strategist Domdora: "You're so pitiful it's an eyesore. I can hardly
bear to look at you."
Strategist Domdora: "I'll put you out of your misery quickly."
Strategist Domdora: "Goodbye. Hero of justice, Pony-Celes."

The news of Pony-Celes's defeat by Zaidarg-G was quickly spread
throughout Japan by the combatants.

The city was dominated by anxiety and fear, and before long, the
complete revival of Dargnoa was accomplished.
One by one, the townspeople were turned into combatants.

There was a boy who resisted until the end, but that boy continued to
shout the name of Pony-Celes--

While being broadcast live nationwide, he was publicly executed as an
example.

Strategist Domudora: "My plans, my ambitions... to be thwarted by such
a person!"

???: "As expected of Pony-Celes, it seems you didn't go down
together."
???: "You need to try a bit harder. President Tsukeshiba."
Plotting General Carine: "My name is Carine."

Plotting General Carine: "I have been directly ordered by Lord Dargnoa
to dispose of Pony-Celes."

Tsukeshiba: "Carine? I don't know anyone by that name, but if you're
here to help, I'm grateful. Quickly, finish off Pony-Celes!"
Pony-Celes: "So you're eager to fight. Good! Come at me!"

Plotting General Carine: "Was it a knife through the heart? Just like
your father, right?"
Tsukeshiba: "...Dargnoa damn... such a little girl..."

Plotting General Carine: "Lord Dargnoa has allowed my talents to
blossom. Unlike you, who are useless."
Tsukeshiba: "How dare you... I... you traitor... wretch..."

Plotting General Carine: "Which mouth is saying that, I wonder?
Betrayal is your specialty, isn't it?"

Plotting General Carine: "However, to think that you wouldn't die from
a stab to the heart, I underestimated the vitality of a cockroach."
Plotting General Carine: "I'll have to finish you off properly."

Tsukeshiba: "Hey, st-stop it! If it's the stone you want, I'll return
it. I'll give it back! Just spare my life!!"

Plotting General Carine: "I don't need such a stone anymore. You can
have that trash. As long as I have this body given to me by Lord
Dargnoa, I am satisfied."

Plotting General Carine: "You're such an eyesore. Just disappear from
my sight already."
Pony-Celes: "What kind of person... to do this to a comrade..."

Plotting General Carine: "Since you didn't finish him off quickly
enough, I did it for you."

Plotting General Carine: "If you hate \n[6] for being kidnapped,
there's no need for restraint."
Plotting General Carine: "Pony-Celes, no... Morisaki Yui!"
Pony-Celes: "Why do you know about me..."
Plotting General Carine: "Heheheh, I know everything about you."

Pony-Celes: "The ace of Shoto Academy's karate club and the annoying
sow who seduced \n[6]."

Plotting General Carine: "If it weren't for you, \n[6] would have been
mine..."

Plotting General Carine: "You're only realizing now? You're as foolish
as ever."
Pony-Celes: "Why! Why would you join Zaidarg!?"
Plotting General Carine: "I'll tell you, you fool."

Plotting General Carine: "That trash from earlier is the very person
who killed my father."

Plotting General Carine: "To take revenge on him, I swore loyalty to
Lord Darnoa and gained power."
Plotting General Carine: "To kill you, whom I despise!"

Plotting General Carine: "I aimed for a mutual takedown using \n[6] as
bait, but unexpectedly, you're quite strong."
Pony-Celes: "So it was you who kidnapped \n[6]."
Pony-Celes: "To think you'd even stage such a drama..."
Plotting General Carine: "Heheh, it's your fault for being deceived."
Pony-Celes: "Please return \n[6]. I'm begging you, Saionji-san..."

Plotting General Carine: "There it is again... 
[6], 
[6], 
[6]...
You really love to irritate me, don't you?"

Plotting General Carine: "I was thinking of killing you right here,
but I've changed my mind."

Plotting General Carine: "Just killing you won't satisfy me. I need to
make you taste the ultimate humiliation."
Pony-Celes: "What are you planning to do?"

Plotting General Carine: "Wait for me in the Grudas district. \n[6] is
there."

Plotting General Carine: "While witnessing \n[6]'s pitiful state, you
will grovel before me."

Pony-Celes: "It's not too late to change things, please don't let your
heart be stolen by Zaidarg... I'm begging you."
Pony-Celes: "I don't want to hurt you..."

Plotting General Carine: "You're worried about me after I took away
someone important to you?"

Plotting General Carine: "Your naivety is astonishing to the point of
being laughable."

Pony-Celes: "I didn't realize how much pain I was causing you... I
failed to notice your loneliness, Saionji-san."

Plotting General Carine: "Shut up! It's all too late now. I won't stop
until I've cast you into hell!"
